completedorder.description: The table records financial transactions, detailing each order by its unique ID, the account ID from which the payment is made, the bank and account number to which the payment is sent, the amount of the transaction, and the type of payment, such as "Household Payment" or "Loan Payment".

CRM Events.description: This table records consumer complaints about financial products and services, detailing the type of product, specific issue, how the complaint was submitted, the company's response, and whether the response was timely or disputed, along with unique identifiers for the complaint and the client.

completeddisposition.description: The table lists the associations between display IDs (disp_id), client IDs (client_id), and account IDs (account_id), specifying the role (type) of each client as either an 'Owner' or a 'User' of the corresponding account.

completedcard.description: The table records details of VISA Signature card transactions, including a unique card identifier (card_id), a display identifier (disp_id), the type of card, and the date of the transaction broken down by year, month, day, and a full date format.

LuxuryLoanPortfolio.description: The table appears to be a record of boat loans, including loan IDs, funded amounts, funding dates, loan durations in years and months, 10-year treasury index rates at funding, interest rates, monthly payments, total past payments, remaining loan balances, property values, and borrower information (names, social security numbers, phone numbers, job titles, and employment lengths). It also includes details about the properties tied to the loans, such as building class categories, tax classes, addresses, zip codes, cities, states, total units, land and gross square footage, and tax class at the time of sale.

CRM Call Center Logs.description: This table appears to record details of customer service calls, including the date received, complaint ID, client identifier, phone number, service line, call ID, priority level, type of call, outcome, server name, service start and exit times, and total service time.

completedloan.description: The table lists details of various loans, including a unique loan ID, associated account ID, loan amount, duration in months, monthly payment amount, loan status, and the full date of loan issuance (broken down by year, month, and day). Additionally, it includes the location code and the purpose of the loan, which in the previewed rows is for purchasing a car.

completeddistrict.description: The table lists various districts, each identified by a unique district_id, along with corresponding city names, state names, state abbreviations, regional classifications, and divisions within the United States.

completedtrans.description: The table records credit transactions made in cash to various accounts, detailing transaction IDs, account IDs, amounts, balances, and timestamps (date and time) for each transaction in the year 2013. Each row includes identifiers, transaction types, and the exact date and time when the transaction occurred.

CRM Reviews.description: This table contains customer reviews for Eagle National Mortgage, including the date of the review, the star rating given (out of 5), the content of the review, the specific product mentioned, and the district ID associated with the review.

completedacct.description: The table lists account details including account ID, district ID, the frequency of issuance, and the parsed date of issuance broken down by year, month, and day for various accounts, with the first five rows showing issuances that occurred at the beginning of January 2013.

completedclient.description: The table contains personal information for clients, including client ID, sex, full date of birth, day, month, year, age, social security number, first, middle, and last names, phone number, email address, residential address with address line 1 and 2, city, state, zipcode, and district ID.
